 - I thought it was very rough at the time. I - at that time of day 'course I was in His Majesty's Forces then I come home to see to things and I went and my pay was three shillings a day then and I went round to see Mr Mercer the Guardian and he asked me
 what I was prepared to leave. I said, you - you've asked me a question like that I said and you see I'm a soldier - I'm in uniform. How much do you think I can earn. He told me not to be cheeky. Eventually he allowed mum ten bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4657134 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13590813\charrsid161096 Was that for the whole family?
